 A BOAT believed to be that of a missing sailor has been found in the Western Isles. 
The man failed to return after setting off from Brevig on the Isle of Lewis in his home-made vessel yesterday morning.
 Stornoway Coastguard launched a major search after a call from concerned relatives at about 8pm last night. 
The missing man did not give details of where he intended to go and does not have a radio or mobile phone with him.
It is understood his three-metre blue and black boat was found earlier today.
A spokeswoman for the Maritime and Coastguard Agency said the search was continuing.
